values:
Oh. My. Giddy. God.

I'm in love with Seth Cohen from the OC. How the hell did this happen?????????

 Well, really it's because I was bored and watched an episode of the OC where Seth makes an X-Men reference. Yuuuup, that's probably what started it. But I was also in love with Adam Brody too....

Hmmmmmm....all I know is I've started watching the OC and I love it. It's weird, in this totally bizarre way because I refused to watch it before but now it's Laguna Beach I refuse to watch.


Oh God, this better not mean that one day I'll actually like Laguna Beach, does it? *shivers*




AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!!!!!!!!!!!!

I just have some birthday wishes for some very special people. Not to steal Eleniel's idea but this is just because someone who's very special to me, her birthday is today. 

HAPPY BIRTHDAY CHARLIE SHEEN! I'm sure you know him from Two and a Half Men, if not...watch the show. It's so FUNNY! He turns 42 today!

HAPPY BIRTHDAY GARRETT HEDLUND! He turns 23 and played Jack Mercer in the action movie Four Brothers and Murtagh in the disaster movie Eragon. xD

HAPPY BIRTHDAY CLARE KRAMER! This beautiful actress played the fiery diva/hell goddess, Glorificus or Glory in Season 5 of Buffy the Vampire Slayer. Clare turns 33 today!

And last but not least, I'd like to wish my Aunt Dora from Milan a very happy birthday. Buon Cumpleano Zia!!!

Well so Eleniel gave me a letter and it's N. Fuck, this is gonna be hard. I'll try to think of ten things. But if not, oh well..

1. Nick Holte (I don't actually know who he is but I got it from Supernatural ^ ^ Gotta love Dean)
2. Nat Black (it's ME! Or rather my mary-sue! Teehee!)
3. Narnia (because i've been reading the Chronicles of Narnia books. I'm on Horse and His Boy ^_^)
4. Naruto (i know it's a crappy ninja anime but Sakura is so FUNNY! ^ ^)
5. Nala (from the Lion King. I LOVE DISNEY! wooT!)
6. Neverland (Peter Pan was my favourite story as a child, besides Little Mermaid. I always wanted to go to Neverland and I don't mean Micheal Jackson's pedophile park)
7. Nyx (Goddess of the Night. She's a character in this book I'm reading called Marked)
8. Natasha Bedingfield (I have her CD and love her songs! The lyrics read like a poem ^ ^)
9. Noob (in honour of my friend the Noobsauce Fairy)
10. Nerds (because they are a yummy candy and also in one of the greatest movies of all times: Revenge of the Nerds.)



Wow, that was fun..... We should definitely do this again sometime.
So, I was looking through all my old stuff and found this totally awesome banner I made! I am so proud of it!

Well here are the promised Drusilla icons. They aren't that great, mostly because I don't have Photoshop or Paintshop Pro so I did them all on regular paint. I'll keep on practicing and maybe someday they won't look as bad.

^_^
